> Anyhow I see the problem with the config file, the root storage.conf file is not used for the rootless users except the rootless_storage_path option. The config file must be created in ~/.config/containers/storage.conf as rootless in order for the mount options to take effect.

@Luap99 since when has this been the case? Looking at the [rootless tutorial](https://github.com/containers/podman/blob/main/docs/tutorials/rootless_tutorial.md#storageconf) storage.conf section, it says there that Podman reads `/etc/containers/storage.conf` in any case, but for rootless setups just ignores the `graphroot` and `runroot` settings there.

I've never had any rootless-specific config files (`containers.conf`, `storage.conf` or `registries.conf`) under `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/containers` on any of my servers. I know that I manually set `driver` to `overlay` back in the 4.x days in `/etc/containers/storage.conf` for my rootless containers, and it had the desired effect.
